President Obama expresses his deep sadness over the passing of White House staffer, Jake Brewer. He describes Jake as one of the best advisors, with a brilliant mind, a big heart, and a strong desire to give back. Jake dedicated his life to empowering people, making government more effective, and advocating for transparency and opportunity for all. The President acknowledges the impact Jake had on society and emphasizes the potential of the younger generation to make a difference. He offers his condolences to Jake's family, particularly his wife, Mary Katharine Ham, and their daughter, Georgia. The President assures them that they will always have a family at the White House.